# Project Instructions — Monolith-Enabled

This project uses the **Monolith** plugin for Unreal Engine MCP integration.

## Available MCP Tools

Monolith exposes ~14 namespace tools with 177 total actions:

- `monolith_discover(namespace?)` — List available actions (call this first)
- `monolith_status()` — Health check, index status, version
- `monolith_reindex()` — Trigger full project re-index
- `monolith_update(action)` — Check for / install plugin updates
- `blueprint_query(action, params)` — Blueprint graph inspection (6 actions)
- `material_query(action, params)` — Material editing, creation, instances, parameters (25 actions)
- `animation_query(action, params)` — Animation asset workflows, PoseSearch (67 actions)
- `niagara_query(action, params)` — Niagara particle systems (41 actions)
- `editor_query(action, params)` — Build, logs, compile output, crash context (13 actions)
- `config_query(action, params)` — Config/INI resolution (6 actions)
- `source_query(action, params)` — Engine source lookup (10 actions)
- `project_query(action, params)` — Deep project index search (5 actions)

## Workflow

1. Use `monolith_discover("namespace")` to see available actions before calling
2. Use `project_query("search", {"query": "..."})` to find assets across the project
3. Use domain-specific tools to inspect and modify assets
4. Use `editor_query("get_build_errors")` after builds to diagnose issues

## Asset Path Conventions

All asset paths use `/Game/Path/To/Asset` format (no `.uasset` extension):
- Project `Content/`: `/Game/Path/To/Asset`
- Project `Plugins/`: `/PluginName/PluginName/Path/To/Asset`
- Engine plugins: `/PluginName/Path/To/Asset`

## Rules

- Always discover available actions before guessing action names
- The project index is pre-built — use `project_query` for broad searches
- Engine source lookups via `source_query` work offline against the local index
- Never guess `#include` paths or function signatures — use `source_query` to verify
- After modifying C++, check build results with `editor_query("get_build_errors")`
